$ Excel functions: aggregate and subTotal

{ funcNum

  table { lrr

                   ☰ `aggregate` ☰ `subTotal`
    average        ☰   1 ☰  1
    count          ☰   2 ☰  2
    countA         ☰   3 ☰  3
    max            ☰   4 ☰  4
    min            ☰   5 ☰  5
    product        ☰   6 ☰  6
    stddev.s       ☰   7 ☰  7
    stddev.p       ☰   8 ☰  8
    sum            ☰   9 ☰  9
    var.s          ☰  10 ☰ 10
    var.p          ☰  11 ☰ 11
    median         ☰  12 ☰ 
    mode.sngl      ☰  13 ☰ 
    large          ☰  14 ☰
    small          ☰  15 ☰
    percentile.inc ☰  16 ☰
    quartile.inc   ☰  17 ☰
    percentile.exc ☰  18 ☰
    quartile.exc   ☰  19 ☰

  table }

  `subTotal` allows to add 100 to its function number which causes the function to not ignore hidden rows (or columns). With 100 added, it behaves equal to `aggregate`

}

